name: Patient Clinical Model 1.0
description: Initial release of PIQI patient model

modelAttributes.name: test
modelAttributes.description: Analysis of specimens derived from humans which provide information for the diagnosis, prevention, treatment of disease, or assessment of health.

modelAttributes.name: resultValue
modelAttributes.description: Documented findings of a tested specimen including structured components

modelAttributes.name: resultUnit
modelAttributes.description: Unit of measurement to report quantitative values.

modelAttributes.name: referenceRange
modelAttributes.description: Upper and lower limit of quantitative test values expected for a designated population of individuals.

modelAttributes.name: interpretation
modelAttributes.description: Categorical assessment of a laboratory value, often in relation to a test's reference range

modelAttributes.name: resultStatus
modelAttributes.description: State or condition of a laboratory test.

modelAttributes.name: specimenCondition
modelAttributes.description: Information regarding a specimen, including the container, that does not meet a laboratoryâ€™s criteria for acceptability.

modelDataClasses.name: DiagnosticImaging
modelDataClasses.description: Tests that result in visual images requiring interpretation by a credentialed professional.

modelAttributes.name: procedure
modelAttributes.description: Procedure that generate visual images (e.g., radiographic, photographic, video) and require interpretation by qualified professionals.

modelAttributes.name: interpretation
modelAttributes.description: Interpreted results of imaging tests. Includes structured and unstructured components.

modelAttributes.name: hasAttachment
modelAttributes.description: Indicated that the imaging report contains a digital attachment (true,false) set by converter

modelDataClasses.name: ClinicalDocuments
modelDataClasses.description: Included all non-labresult and structured findings - can represent general clinical documents, imaging and clinical test (like EKG)

modelAttributes.name: hasAttachment
modelAttributes.description: Indicated that a document has a digital attachment (true or false) populated by converter

modelDataClasses.name: Encounters
modelDataClasses.description: Information related to interactions between healthcare providers and a patient

modelAttributes.name: encounterType
modelAttributes.description: Category of health care service. (e.g., office visit, telephone assessment, home visit)

modelAttributes.name: encounterDiagnosis
modelAttributes.description: Coded diagnoses associated with an episode of care.

modelAttributes.name: encounterIdentifier
modelAttributes.description: Sequence of characters by which an encounter is known.

modelDataClasses.name: Goals
modelDataClasses.description: Desired state to be achieved by a person or a personâ€™s elections to guide care.

modelAttributes.name: goal
modelAttributes.description: SDOH goals, Treatable Prevention Preferences, Care Experience Preferences, etc.

modelAttributes.name: goalCategory
modelAttributes.description: Indicates a category the goal falls within.

modelAttributes.name: goalStatus
modelAttributes.description:
Describes the progression, or lack thereof, towards the goal against the target
in-progress | improving | worsening | no-change | achieved | sustaining | not-achieved | no-progress | not-attainable

modelAttributes.name: goalPriority
modelAttributes.description: Identifies the mutually agreed level of importance associated with reaching/sustaining the goal
